com.thinkaurelius.titan.core
Interface TitanQuery

All Superinterfaces:
com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Query
public interface TitanQuery
extends com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Query

TitanQuery constructs and executes a query over incident edges from the perspective of a vertex. A TitanQuery extends Blueprint's Query by some Titan specific convenience methods. Using TitanQuery proceeds in two steps: 1) Define the query by specifying what to retrieve and 2) execute the query.
A TitanQuery is initialized by calling TitanTransaction.query(long) with an existing vertex id or TitanVertex.query() on the vertex itself.

Author:
Matthias Bröcheler (http://www.matthiasb.com)

has

TitanQuery has(TitanType type,
               Object value)
Query only for edges that have an incident property or unidirected edge matching the given value. If type is a property key, then the query is restricted to edges having an incident property matching this key-value pair. If type is an edge label, then it is expected that this label is unidirected (TitanLabel.isUnidirected() and the query is restricted to edges having an incident unidirectional edge pointing to the value which is expected to be a TitanVertex.

Parameters:
type - TitanType
value - Value for the property of the given key to match, or vertex to point unidirectional edge to
Returns:
this query

inMemory

TitanQuery inMemory()
Configures the query for in-memory retrieval. By default, an implementation of TitanQuery chooses the most efficient way to retrieve a vertex's incident relations. In some cases, it may be most efficient to NOT create the object graph in memory but only retrieve what is asked for (e.g. vertex ids) directly from the storage backend. However, when the same or similar queries are repeatedly executed, creating the object graph in memory first is more efficient. Calling this method signals such cases to the TitanQuery implementation. By default, the in memory retrieval flag is false.

Returns:
this query

vertexIds

VertexList vertexIds()
Retrieves all vertices connected to this query's central vertex by edges matching the conditions defined in this query. No guarantee is made as to the order in which the vertices are listed. Use VertexList.sort() to sort by vertex ids most efficiently. The query engine will determine the most efficient way to retrieve the vertices that match this query.

Specified by:
vertexIds in interface com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Query
Returns:
A list of all vertices connected to this query's central vertex by matching edges
